radiographic_examinations.findings: Abnormal bronchial bifurcation originating in the right main bronchus.
Yellow, serous secretions from an anomalous orifice in the medial side of the right intermediate bronchus.
Contrast material slowly proceeding to the hepatic region.
Small amount of air and contrast material remaining in the liver.
Most of the radionuclide accumulated in the normal biliary pathway and a small amount in the fistula.
